name: p-hydroxy butyl benzoate
Reason: The compound p-hydroxy butyl benzoate consists of a benzene ring, hydroxyl (-OH), ester (benzoate), and a butyl chain. Considering these functional group effects cumulatively, we predict the melting point of p-hydroxy butyl benzoate.
Prediction: The melting point of p-hydroxy butyl benzoate is predicted to be 5.5 (benzene) + 80 (hydroxyl group) + 50 (ester group) - 20 (butyl group) = 115.5°C
